  <span class="header_d line-bg">1970s</span>
  <h2 class="header_b">LAYING THE GROUNDWORK</h2>
  
  <p class="common-margin">In 1973, the first seedlings were planted at the Brancott Estate Vineyard. After two years of mixed success, we rethought tradition to take our vines in a new direction – literally. Thanks to the     region's sunny days and crisp nights, our grapes developed a unique and fresh flavour profile – and by 1979 Marlborough's first ever Sauvignon Blanc was born.
  </p>
