  <span class="header_d line-bg">1980s</span>
  <h2 class="header_b">LAYING THE GROUNDWORK</h2>
  <p>After our first release of Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc won Gold at the 1980 New Zealand Easter Show, we followed this with an equally successful first release of Fumé Blanc. Meanwhile, Marlborough was making a name for itself on the world stage, and the early 80s saw our first export of wine overseas, as well as the first ever shipment of Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc to the UK. By the end of the decade, our Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc was selected from more than 1100 Sauvignon Blancs to win the Marquis de Goulaine trophy at the 21st International Wine & Spirit Competition. 
  </p>
  
