  <span class="header_d line-bg">1990s</span>
  <h2 class="header_b">LAYING THE GROUNDWORK</h2>
 
  <p class="common-margin">1990 brought two very special people to our home. Firstly, Her Majesty, Queen Elizabeth II visited the Brancott Estate vineyard and planted a vine. Secondly, the team welcomed Patrick Materman, who would go on to become our Chief Winemaker. By the middle of the decade, we became the first Australasian winery to win an ISO 9001 global quality accreditation. Meanwhile, winemaker Andy Frost won White Winemaker of the Year and our 1996 Marlborough Chardonnay was voted International Wine of the Year at the London International Wine Challenge.
  </p>
