  <span class="header_d line-bg">2000s</span>
  <h2 class="header_b">…while nurturing our roots</h2>
  <p class="common-margin">After becoming a founding member of Sustainable Winegrowing New Zealand, Brancott Estate became the world's first winery to install tipping tanks, allowing us to naturally extract even more goodness from each grape. We also became the first wine company in New Zealand to achieve five top international industry standards relating to quality, environment, health and safety. 2001 saw Patrick Materman win Winestate Magazine’s New Zealand Winemaker of the Year award, and our Vineyard continued to grow, with the first vintage of Sauvignon Gris in Marlborough.
  </p>
  
 
  
